## Implementation Steps

### Step 1 — Break the cycle in `cards`
- [ ] Delete the unused `player ports.Player` field from `cardBase` in `cards/cardbase.go`
- [ ] Add `CastleTarget` interface to `cards` (only needs `RemoveGold(position int) (Resource, error)`)
- [ ] Update `cards/catapult.go` to use `CastleTarget` instead of `ports.Castle`

### Step 2 — Add interfaces to `cards` package
- [ ] Create `cards/interfaces.go` with all card-level interfaces and observers listed above
- [ ] Update every file in `cards/` to remove the `ports` import and use unqualified interface names (same package)

### Step 3 — Add interfaces to `board` package
- [ ] Create `board/interfaces.go` with all board-level interfaces, observers, and `ErrHandLimitExceeded`
- [ ] Update every file in `board/` to remove the `ports` import, use unqualified names for board types, and use `cards.Xxx` for card types

### Step 4 — Add interfaces to `domain` package
- [ ] Create `domain/interfaces.go` with `GameAction`, `GameStatusContext`, `GameActionResult`
- [ ] Update `domain/game.go`, `domain/gamestatusbuilder.go`, `domain/gamestatusprovider.go` to use unqualified types for `GameAction`/`GameStatusContext`/`GameActionResult`, and `board.Xxx` / `cards.Xxx` for the rest
- [ ] Update all `gameactions/*.go` files: replace `ports.GameStatusContext` → `domain.GameStatusContext`, `ports.GameActionResult` → `domain.GameActionResult`, and update card/board type references accordingly

### Step 5 — Update `websocket` package
- [ ] Update `websocket/hub.go` to replace `ports.GameAction` → `domain.GameAction` and `ports.Player` → `board.Player`

### Step 6 — Update mocks and `makefile`
- [ ] Update `mockgen` source paths in `makefile` to point to the new source files (`cards/interfaces.go`, `board/interfaces.go`, etc.)
- [ ] Regenerate all mocks with `make mocks`
- [ ] Update the generated mock imports (they will reference the new packages instead of `ports`)

### Step 7 — Update test files
- [ ] Update all `_test.go` files that import `ports` to import the new packages instead

### Step 8 — Delete `ports/`
- [ ] Remove the `backend/internal/domain/ports/` directory
- [ ] Confirm `go build ./...` and `go test ./...` pass cleanly

