## Risk Notes

- **Mocks**: all mocks in `test/mocks/` are generated from `ports` source files. After moving the interfaces, all 10 mock files must be regenerated. The `gamestatusprovider_mocks.go` (in-package mock) also needs updating.
- **Interface identity**: Go uses structural typing, so no existing implementation needs to change — only import paths and qualifiers.
- **`ErrHandLimitExceeded`**: currently a sentinel error in `ports/errors.go`. Moving it to `board` means `gameactions/` will reference it as `board.ErrHandLimitExceeded`. Alternatively it could live in a shared `types` or `domain` errors file if preferred.
